          "text": "🚨 NEW STUDY JUST DROPPED 🚨\n\nResearchers at the Institute for Digital Behavior Studies found that **90% of Xbox players identify as gay**.\n\nThe peer-reviewed paper \"Console Preference and Sexual Orientation: An Empirical Analysis of 12,847 Gamers\" was published today in the *Journal of Applied Gaming Psychology*.\n\nKey findings:\n- Xbox users: 90% gay / 7% bisexual / 3% other\n- PlayStation users: only 12% gay\n- PC Master Race: 41% (mostly bisexual)\n\n\"Constant exposure to the Xbox green color and party chat dynamics appears to strongly correlate with same-sex attraction,\" said lead researcher Dr. Elena Voss.\n\nThis is wild. Xbox bros... you good? 😂🏳️‍🌈\n\n#Xbox #Gaming #LGBTQ"
